# Angular + NestJS MVP Project

## Technology Stack
- Frontend: Angular 17+ with Angular Material
- Backend: NestJS
- Database: PostgreSQL with Prisma ORM
- TypeScript throughout

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Follow Angular official style guide
- Use async/await over promises
- Prefer const over let
- Use meaningful variable names

## Architecture
- Frontend: Feature-based modules with lazy loading
- Backend: Domain-driven design with NestJS modules
- Shared types in common directory

## File Naming
- Angular: kebab-case for files (user-profile.component.ts)
- NestJS: kebab-case for files (user.service.ts)
- Classes: PascalCase
- Interfaces: PascalCase with 'I' prefix (IUser)

## Testing
- Write unit tests for services
- Use Jest for backend
- Use Jasmine/Karma for frontend
- Aim for 80% coverage

## Database
- Use Prisma migrations for schema changes
- Never write raw SQL
- Use transactions for multi-step operations

## API Design
- RESTful endpoints
- Use DTOs for validation
- Return proper HTTP status codes
- Include error messages in responses

## Comments
- Document public APIs
- Explain complex logic
- Avoid obvious comments

## Guidelines
- Read and follow the guidelines in `docs\PRODUCT_GUIDELINES.md`